Pomminryon south headquarters issues statement
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;   Pyongyang, July 3 (KCNA) -- The south headquarters of the National Alliance for the Country's Reunification (Pomminryon) recently issued a statement on the tense situation  prevailing in Korea due to the armed conflict sparked by the South Korean authorities in the West Sea of Korea at the instigation of the U.S.  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
A very tense situation has been created in this land due to the premeditated and intentional incident caused by the United States and the present "government" in the west sea, the statement said.   It denounced before all the countries and nations of the world the heinous plot of the United States and the present "government"  to start a war on the Korean peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  It continued:   We call upon all the countries and peoples of the world to voice active support and solidarity with us in the struggle for reconciliation, unity and reunification of the north and south.  We appeal to the pro-reunification patriotic organizations, figures and people to rise up in a sacred war against the United States, the struggle to oust present "government" and the struggle for reunification.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The statement demanded a prompt repeal of the "5027-98  Korean war plan" that has  entered a phase of its implementation, a signing of a peace agreement between the north and the U.S. and an immediate withdrawal of the U.S. forces and war means from South Korea.

S. Korean rulers urged to discontinue anti-north false propaganda
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 3 (KCNA) -- Strange voices are ringing out from South Korea as regards the Min  Yong Mi case.   The South Korean authorities asserted that the north threatened Min  Yong Mi and forced her to write a letter of apology, thus reducing her to an operative for defection on purpose.   As exposed clearly, the South Korean authorities sent Min  Yong Mi as a tourist to Mt. Kumgang for the purpose of inducing persons in the north  to defect to the south. This is an intolerable criminal act.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Min  should have been punished by our law for the gravity of her crime but the DPRK government took a lenient step to send her back to South Korea.   The South Korean authorities, however, are getting frantic again in the anti-north false propaganda, asserting that the north threatened her to write a letter of apology and there should be a safety guarantee for tourists in the future. This added to their criminal provocations against the north.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   From a compatriotic stand, we let Min  put up at a deluxe hotel and treated her well. Moved by this hospitality, she voluntarily admitted all the grave political crimes committed by her and entreated for lenient pardon.   Min  went back to South Korea safe. But the South Korean authorities is using her for the anti-communist propaganda again. It is not quite surprising.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   We will, in the future, too, greet and welcome with compatriotic feelings all the fellow tourists who come to see Mt. Kumgang  with their wholeheart without any sinister aim and purpose.   We will, in the future, not send back such impure elements as Min  Yong Mi for good and all. The South Korean authorities  should be wholly responsible for all the consequences to be entailed therefrom.   We will strictly punish such impure elements as Min  Yong Mi trying to  hatch anti-north plots under the mask of tourists.

"Complete Collection of Kim Il Sung's Works" vol. 26 off press 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 3 (KCNA) -- The volume 26 of "Complete Collection of Kim Il Sung's Works" was published by the Worker's Party of Korea Publishing House recently.
   The volume consists of 26 enduring works, including the historic speeches, conclusions and talks, which the President Kim Il Sung made between September Juche 49 (1960) and March Juche 50 (1961).&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Expounded in the works are the unique ideas, theories and policies President Kim Il Sung advanced in order to further strengthen the party, dynamically step up the socialist construction and further consolidate the revolutionary base politically, economically and militarily on the basis of his scientific  insight into the requirements of the developing Korean revolution and the  trends of the situation from a steadfast Juche-based viewpoint and stand.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Also laid down in the works are outstanding ideas, theories and policies that give flawless scientific answers to theoretical and practical issues arising in the revolution and construction, including the issue of intensifying the struggle to attain national reunification, the nation's supreme task, and the issue of giving momentum to the movement of Koreans in Japan.

Military attaches corps visits  Mangyongdae
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 3 (KCNA) -- The military attaches corps here visited Mangyongdae on Thursday on the occasion of the 5th anniversary of the President Kim Il Sung's demise.   Being briefed on the glorious revolutionary history of the President, the guests looked round the relics preserved at his native home and inspected the revolutionary relics on Mangyong Hill.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   After the visit, Vu Dinh Thang, military attach of the Vietnam embassy and doyen of the military attaches  corps,  said that time-honored Mangyongdae where the President  cultivated his great will for revolution is an important place  for revolutionary education of the people.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The  military attaches corps went to see the international friendship exhibition on Friday.  Military attaches admiringly looked round the gifts  presented to the President, by foreign party and state leaders, prominent political and public figures and people of different social standings.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Alfonso Rodriguez Perez, military attach  of the Cuban embassy, said that gifts from U.S. public figures were also put on show, which tells how absolute the authority of  President Kim Il Sung is.

U.S. aggression and war moves denounced
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 3 (KCNA) -- A joint statement condemning the ever intensified U.S. aggression and war moves was issued on June 10 in Havana, Cuba, by the Communist Party of Paraguay, the Salvadoran Farabundo Marti National Liberation Front, the Independent Movement of Puerto Rico, the Communist Party of Argentine, the Palestine Liberation Democratic Front and the Communist Party of Colombia.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The statement said that the U.S. is amassing armed forces on a large scale in the Korean peninsula and the far east and put them on a war-footing under the pretext of filling up the "military vacuum" caused by the Yugoslav incident and is creating a touch-and-go  situation by staging ceaseless war exercises and military provocations.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It continued:   The U.S. is hell-bent on arms buildup and war exercises to put into practice the "operation plan 5027-98", a war scenario for invading the north. This is the revelation of its heinous intention to Ohen a decisive phase for igniting a nuclear war in the Korean peninsula and dominating Asia.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The statement urged the U.S. to take hands of domination and interference off South Korea, promptly stop the arms buildup and war exercises aimed at invading the north and withdraw its troops and nuclear weapons  from South Korea at once.

S. Korean people's struggle supported
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 3 (KCNA) -- A "solidarity meeting for supporting the struggle of the South Korean people for independence, democracy and reunification" was held in Havana on June 9 under the sponsorship of the Organization of Solidarity of the Peoples of Africa, Asia and Latin America on the occasion of the 30th anniversary of the foundation of the National Democratic Front of South Korea (NDFSK).&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Ramon Pees Ferro, secretary general of the executive secretariat of the organization, in a report said that the valiant struggle waged by the Korean people against the U.S. imperialism and Japanese militarism in the past greatly inspired the progressive humankind struggling against the U.S. ambition to dominate the world.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The United States is, indeed, a obstacle  lying in the way of achieving peace and reunification of the Korean peninsula, he noted, demanding a termination of the U.S. domination over and intervention in South Korea, withdrawal of the U.S. forces and nuclear weapons from there, abolish of the "National Security Law" of South Korea and dissolution of the U.S.-Japan-South Korea triangular military alliance.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Pak Kwang Gi, head of a delegation of the NDFSK, speaking at the meeting, expressed the expectation that political parties and organizations of different countries of the world would extend active support and encouragement to the South Korean people in their struggle for independence, democracy and unification this year which marks the 30th anniversary of the foundation of the NDFSK.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Speeches were made by delegates of the Communist Party of the Peoples of Spain, the Palestine Liberation Democratic Front and six other  political parties and fronts.   A "final declaration supporting the South Korean people in their struggle for independence, democracy and reunification" was adopted at the meeting.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The declaration urged the United States to wash its hands of domination over and intervention in South Korea and immediately withdraw its forces and nuclear weapons from there. It resolutely opposed a new military alliance among the U.S., Japan and South Korea with the U.S. as an axis.   It also demanded the South Korean authorities abolish the "National Security Law" which blocks inter-Korean contacts.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It supported the struggle of the NDFSK and all the patriotic forces in South Korea for independence against imperialism, for democratization against fascism and for the national reunification.

Epic dedicated to anniversary of Kim Il Sung's demise
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 3 (KCNA) -- "May history of comradeship last forever," an epic dedicated to the 5th anniversary of the President Kim Il Sung's demise, was carried in Rodong Sinmun Friday.   The epic says that the history of comradeship was started in Korea by President Kim Il Sung and that his whole life was dedicated to comrades.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Dealing with the comradely relationship between the president and anti-Japanese revolutionary fighters and peoples from all walks of life, it stresses his comradeship was as wide as universal, irrespective of nationality and border.   It also says the history of comradeship, a revolutionary legacy of the president, continues under the dynamic guidance of General Secretary Kim Jong Il.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Kim Jong Il is identical to the president in terms of his love and trust in comrades and helis the supreme incarnation of comradeship who leads tens of millions of people in this country along the road of revolution, regarding them as his comrades, the epic says.   It is thanks to his guidance that the history of comradeship is going on and the country boasts these ranks of loyal and filial subjects, it notes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It is his unshakable will to build a strong and prosperous nation and achieve the final victory of the Korean revolution on the basis of comradeship, and it is the Korean people's will to remain unboundedly loyal to him and become his comrades, it concludes.

Studying while on job
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 3 (KCNA) -- In the DPRK, all the working people are enrolled in the well-arranged part-time system of higher education.   The major industrial establishments have their own colleges, while minor ones have branches and field classes of factory colleges. After the day's work, the workers attend classes to master modern science and technology. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  There are also on-going farm and fishermen's colleges. All ocean-going vessels are fitted with lecture rooms for fishermen.   Commuter trains are in the service of education for correspondence courses.-   The  first factory college came into being on July 15, 1951 in the thick of the Korean war (June 25, 1950-July 27, 1953) and it has since multiplied into more than 100.  These factory colleges produce a large number of technicians every year.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   For example, the Ryongsong College of Machinery affiliated with the Ryongsong Associated Machinery Bureau has so far produced some 1,500 technicians. These graduates, who have acquired wide-ranging latest know how, have greatly contributed to designing and manufacturing made-to-order equipment such as a 10,000-ton press and large lathes. Some of them have been honored with the titles of labour hero, people's and merited designers, and more than 10 workers are the holders of academic degrees and titles.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The Ryongyang College of Technology UT the Ryongyang Mine has trained as many miners into engineers. It is credited with producing the greater bulk of the mine's management and technical staff.   The graduates of factory colleges have provided a worthy help to the national economy with their technical discoveries accounting for tens of thousands.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Not long ago, a whole work-team consisting of discharged soldiers on the Kumsan Cooperative Farm in Paechon county, South Hwanghae Province, have finished the Kim Je Won Haeju University of Agriculture through correspondence course and become agronomists.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Those people produced from the part-time system of high education make up a large proportion of the nearly two million intellectuals, the ultra-dynamics of the building of a powerful nation.
